Class Evaluator

  • java.lang.Object
    • metalign.utils.Evaluator

  • public class Evaluator
extends java.lang.Object
    An Evaluator is used to evaluate some voice, beat, and hierarchy hypothesis, given a ground truth file.

        Create a new Evaluator from the given ground truth file. This performs all of the parsing necessary to get the ground truth times, groupings, etc.
        Parameters:
        groundTruth - The ground truth file to parse.
        anacrusisFiles - The anacrusis files to use.
        useChannel - Whether to use channels or tracks for MIDI voices.

        java.io.IOException
